[30;1m292 | [0m[35m        fact that half of the abscissas at degree `m` are precisely the[0m
[30;1m293 | [0m[35m        abscissas from degree `m-1`. Thus reusing the result from[0m
[30;1m294 | [0m[35m        the previous level allows a 2x speedup.[0m

[30;1m265 | [0m[35m        # Handle the weird types[0m
[30;1m266 | [0m[35m        try: diff = np.abs(type(np.sqrt(x))(sqrt(x)) - np.sqrt(x))[0m
[30;1m267 | [0m[35m        except: continue[0m
[30;1m268 | [0m[35m        assert diff < np.float64(2.0**-53)[0m
[30;1m269 | [0m[35m    assert mpf(np.float64('inf')) == inf[0m
